### USER CHALLENGE #1 — surface at Phase 4 gate
**You said:** "INVARIANTS.md split into 11 PG + 8 UF MVP-Blocking, rest (18 UF) Post-MVP Quality Bar" (CEO phase revision #6)

**Both models recommend:** Promote `UF-02`, `UF-09`, `UF-18`, `UF-24`, `UF-25` back to MVP-Blocking → new split is 11 PG + 13 UF MVP-Blocking, 13 UF Post-MVP.

**Why (both models):** All five are first-run trust load-bearing. UF-24 facts-first is the ChatGPT-differentiator. UF-02 skip prevents field-user churn. Phase 9 already depends on all five, making the current split contradictory.

**What we might be missing:** You wanted a minimal MVP scope to ship the wedge faster. Promoting 5 UFs back extends Phase 9 scope by ~1 week CC effort.

**If we're wrong, cost:** MVP ships faster but with ChatGPT-shape trust debt. Gate 2 (time-to-escalation reduction) may fail because users don't trust facts-first-absent answers.

### USER CHALLENGE #2 — surface at Phase 4 gate
**You said:** Mobile 360x800 one-screen path = `question → 결론 → first citation preview` (CEO phase revision #7)

**Both models recommend:** Two explicit viewport templates — single-law and multi-law — each with facts-first card order matching design doc:172-192, not conclusion-first.

**Why:** Design doc explicitly rejects conclusion-first as "the ChatGPT trap." Multi-law case needs 답변 범위/미답변 범위 banner in the first screen; current mobile spec has no slot for it.

**What we might be missing:** Facts-first + 결론 + citation in one 800px scroll (with IME closed) may not fit, forcing a 2-scroll mobile first screen.

**If we're wrong, cost:** Mobile first-screen compliance test becomes harder to pass. Possible compromise: collapsed verified-facts chip that expands on tap, keeping 결론 visible.

